Deliberate Gentle Love Dreamer (DGLDm)

Steady, reliable, and cradling her tenderly. Take a deep breath, and let it out real easy...you are The Slow Dancer.

Your focus is love, not sex, and for your age, you have average experience. But you're a great, thoughtful guy, and your love life improves every year. There's also a powerful elimination process working in your favor: most Playboy types get stuck raising unwanted kids before you even begin settling down. The women left over will be hot and yours. Your ideal woman is someone intimate, intelligent, and very supportive.

The Hornivore

I just watched an interview with the President of Jefferson Parish, Louisiana, who's elderly mother drowned in her nursing home. She called him every day, asking when someone was going to come save her, and everyday he reassured her (just as he was reassured by his superiors) that someone would be there to save her the next day.

She went the whole week without being saved and drowned in her nursing home Friday night.

He broke down on TV.

He cried his eyes out.

He was more than critical of the inaction in the wake of the storm.


On top of that, I just read an article that was published in the Times-Picayune more than four years ago which predicted this entire scenario down to the last detail.

http://www.nola.com/hurricane/index.ssf?/washingaway/thebigone_1.html

Four years worth of warning.

Four years of inaction.

An estimated 10,000 dead.

How utterly fucking disgusting.


I am so greatful that those I love that are from New Orleans are allright.

I don't know what I'd do if I lost you.


To those that read this:
Please visit http://www.redcross.org/ or call 1(800)HELP-NOW and help those less fortunate than yourselves.

I am going to go say a prayer.
You should too.

what's up loyal readers? this is your narrator here. i've been on hiatus for a little while due to drama and physical injury, but now i'm back. in black. 

anyway, i've got my cell back, so call me, 510-0648. also, i'm the proud owner of a brand spanking new concussion. if you want to find out about it, call me.

also, i'm quite pissed over hearing from good ole stevie that the stupid cunt that i was formerly romantically entangled with gave my oxycontin-addicted cousin his first taste of heroin last weekend. if there's anything i regret doing in my life, its letting her into it, let alone introducing her to my family. she's back to her old bulimic tricks again, so here's hoping she dies slowly and painfully of complications of malnutrition and an overdose.

i should have listened to everyone when they told me not to get involved with Jamie. i broke up with her because i just couldn't deal with another crazy person in my life. her constant neurosis, clinginess, suicide attempts, and various other unnerving behaviour finally got to me. what did she do? she wound up in mobile infirmary's psychiatric ward with a knife wound so deep that she can't feel the fingers on her left hand... i finally severed things with her last night when she called me just to tell me what a horrble person i am. she wrote a nice little entry about it on her livejournal chockfull of psychobabble/propaganda and attack after attack at me. she even called me abusive. after reading it, i realized something that my dad told me from the beginning... "she's just like your mother"... the funny thing is, not long after i started dating her, i started having these attacks that would cause my body to almost shut down and i had to be medicated to counter them. i haven't had one since i got rid of her. to my friends that wouldn't come around thanks to the nutty ball-and-chain... i'm sorry. i'm really genuinely sorry that i didn't listen to you and i'm sorry that i've been sort of gone... i'm back guys...
